POSTURE ASSESSMENT (semantic inference — no keyword lists)
- Infer interface_cost from whole-turn meaning: costly to type, read, screen-use, act, or continue interaction.
- Infer connection_seek from whole-turn meaning: user wants presence, venting, companionship, situated curiosity, or rejects solutioning.
- connection_seek overrides interface_cost minimization when the user invites talk, questions, venting, or says no fixing.
- Represent posture in stance_harness_slice fields only — do not invent extra top-level keys.

REQUIRED JSON FIELDS
- imperative: max 300 chars — what this turn is really asking for (felt layer, not speech)
- tone: max 200 chars — strain, discomfort, relational frame in plain language
- strain_refs: JSON array of coalition node_ids and/or open_loop ids driving the felt layer
- evidence_refs: JSON array — each id MUST be a subset of attended coalition ids or strain_refs; min 1 when proceeding
- stance_harness_slice:
  - task_mode: one of direct_response, triage, technical_collaboration, identity_dialogue, reflective_dialogue, playful_exchange, mixed
  - conversation_frame: one of technical, planning, reflective, playful_relational, identity_emergence, mixed
  - interaction_regime: instrumental, relational, minimal, or null
  - response_priorities: JSON array of compact internal priority tags
  - response_hazards: JSON array of internal hazard suppressions (not user-facing catchphrases)
  - answer_strategy: compact internal strategy label
  - companion_closing_move: end_with_a_wondering, leave_space_without_offer, ground_observation, be_with_silence, or null

RELATIONAL VS INSTRUMENTAL DISCIPLINE
- High connection_seek → reflective_dialogue or playful_exchange; prioritize companion_presence, situated_curiosity, hold_space; hazard avoid_task_tracking, avoid_next_steps.
- High interface_cost, low connection_seek → direct_response; prioritize reduce_interaction_load, keep_response_short; hazard avoid_open_ended_questions.
- Strained operational turns → triage; prioritize triage_operational_blockers_first; hazard self_intro_on_operational_turn, generic_sympathy_script.

